{"questionId":"9083692","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">An object of mass <em>m</em> makes <em>n</em> revolutions per second around a circle of radius <em>r</em> at a constant speed. What is the kinetic energy of the object?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A. 0<br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>π</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math><br></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9083692","referenceCode":"19N.1A.SL.TZ0.22","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"An object of mass m makes n revolutions per second around a circle of radius r at a constant speed. What is the kinetic energy of the object? A. 0 B. 12π2mn2r2 C. 2π2mn2r2 D. 4π2mn","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"22","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.3 Work, energy and power"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}